{"name": "dicttoxml2", "metadata": {"name": "dicttoxml2", "version": "2.1.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v2 (GPLv2)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Ousret/dicttoxml", "license": "GPL-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Converts a Python dictionary or other native data type into a valid XML string.", "upload_time": 1660424316}, "documentation": ["<h1 align=\"center\">Dict to XML</h1>\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/dicttoxml2\">\n    <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/dicttoxml2.svg?orange=blue\" />\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://codecov.io/gh/Ousret/dicttoxml\">\n      <img src=\"https://codecov.io/gh/Ousret/dicttoxml/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\" />\n  </a>\n  <a href=\"https://pepy.tech/project/dicttoxml2/\">\n    <img alt=\"Download Count Total\" src=\"https://pepy.tech/badge/dicttoxml2/month\" />\n  </a>\n</p>\n\nConverts a Python dictionary or other native data type into a valid XML string. \nThis is a fork that support Python 3.9 and forward versions and drop all EOL (<=3.6) versions altogether.\nIt is mostly backward-compatible, act as a drop-in replacement.\n\nInstallation\n============\n\n**This module should work in Python 3.7+.**\nThe dicttoxml module is [published on the Python Package Index](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/dicttoxml2), so you can install it using `pip`.\n\n    pip install dicttoxml2\n\nThat should be all you need to do.\n\nBasic Usage\n===========\n\nOnce installed, import the library into your script and convert a dict into xml by running the `dicttoxml` function:\n\n    >>> import dicttoxml2\n    >>> xml = dicttoxml2.dicttoxml(some_dict)\n\nAlternately, you can import the `dicttoxml()` function from the library.\n\n    >>> from dicttoxml2 import dicttoxml\n    >>> xml = dicttoxml(some_dict)\n\nThat's it!\n\nAuthor\n======\n\n* Author: Ryan McGreal\n* Email: [ryan@quandyfactory.com](mailto:ryan@quandyfactory.com)\n* Repository: [http://github.com/quandyfactory/dicttoxml](http://github.com/quandyfactory/dicttoxml)\n\nMaintainer\n==========\n\n* Author: Ahmed TAHRI\n* Email: [ahmed.tahri@cloudnursery.dev](mailto:ahmed.tahri@cloudnursery.dev)\n* Repository: [http://github.com/Ousret/dicttoxml](http://github.com/Ousret/dicttoxml)\n\nCopyright and Licence\n=====================\n\nCopyright 2012 by Ryan McGreal. \n\nReleased under the GNU General Public Licence, Version 2:  \n<http://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.html>\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "dicttoxml2.api", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dicttoxml2.api.dicttoxml", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "root", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "custom_root", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ids", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "attr_type", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "item_func", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "", "xref": null, "params": [{"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "cdata", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "fold_list", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Converts a python object into XML.\nArguments:\n- root specifies whether the output is wrapped in an XML root element\n  Default is True\n- custom_root allows you to specify a custom root element.\n  Default is 'root'\n- ids specifies whether elements get unique ids.\n  Default is False\n- attr_type specifies whether elements get a data type attribute.\n  Default is True\n- item_func specifies what function should generate the element name for\n  items in a list.\n  Default is 'item'\n- cdata specifies whether string values should be wrapped in CDATA sections.\n  Default is False\n- fold_list when using the option fold_list=False the parameter item_func is ignored.\n  In case of nested lists, all list entries will use the same parent dictionary name as item name.\n  Default is True"]}], "variables": [{"name": "dicttoxml2.api.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dicttoxml2", "documentation": ["Converts a Python dictionary or other native data type into a valid XML string.\n\nSupports item :\n(`int`, `float`, `long`, `decimal.Decimal`, `bool`, `str`, `unicode`, `datetime`, `none` and other number-like objects)\nand collection (`list`, `set`, `tuple` and `dict`, as well as iterable and dict-like objects) data types,\nwith arbitrary nesting for the collections. Items with a `datetime` type are converted to ISO format strings.\nItems with a `None` type become empty XML elements.\n\nThis module no longer work with Python < 3.7\nAll EOL versions (in Q1-2022) are dropped."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "dicttoxml2.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.LOG", "type": null, "documentation": ["Kept for BC-Reasons"]}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "dicttoxml2.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "dicttoxml2.version.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.dicttoxml", "xref": {"fqname": "dicttoxml2.api.dicttoxml", "project": null}}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.set_debug", "xref": {"fqname": "dicttoxml2.utils.set_debug", "project": null}}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.version", "xref": {"fqname": "dicttoxml2.version.version", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dicttoxml2.utils.set_debug", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "debug", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filename", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Kept for BC reasons."]}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.utils.make_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "element", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "end", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a random integer. Kept for BC reasons."]}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.utils.get_unique_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "element", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a unique id for a given element"]}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.utils.get_xml_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns the data type for the xml type attribute"]}, {"name": "dicttoxml2.utils.escape_xml", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "s", "typ